1
00:00:32,208 --> 00:00:34,125
♪

2
00:00:39,291 --> 00:00:41,833
[KAWASE]
This is incredible, Mikazuki!

3
00:00:41,916 --> 00:00:44,458
Your signing event last year
was a huge hit,

4
00:00:44,541 --> 00:00:47,416
and our survey says
the readers love you!

5
00:00:47,500 --> 00:00:50,541
My friend,
this year will be massive!

6
00:00:50,625 --> 00:00:53,500
-[SUBARU] Uh-huh.
-On that note,

7
00:00:53,583 --> 00:00:57,416
it’s about time you finally
get started on your next series!

8
00:00:58,875 --> 00:01:00,250
[SUBARU]
My next series.

9
00:01:00,333 --> 00:01:03,125
I have to keep
the ball rolling, huh?

10
00:01:03,208 --> 00:01:07,625
Well, I have been brainstorming
for a while now.

11
00:01:07,708 --> 00:01:09,000
[inhales sharply]

12
00:01:13,791 --> 00:01:15,583
But I can’t come up
with anything!

13
00:01:15,666 --> 00:01:17,208
My mind is blank!

14
00:01:23,041 --> 00:01:26,875
Did I always have those flowers?

15
00:01:26,958 --> 00:01:28,791
[faucet squeaking]

16
00:01:28,875 --> 00:01:32,833
[water spraying]

17
00:01:32,916 --> 00:01:36,291
[SUBARU] It’s been a month now
since Kawase said that to me.

18
00:01:36,375 --> 00:01:39,916
I’ve been racking my brain day
in and out, but...

19
00:01:40,000 --> 00:01:41,833
[sighs]

20
00:01:45,875 --> 00:01:49,791
The assassin cat’s
next mysterious mission. Hmm...

21
00:01:49,875 --> 00:01:51,333
-[spraying]
-[angry meowing]

22
00:01:52,625 --> 00:01:54,833
[HARU hissing]

23
00:01:54,916 --> 00:01:57,250
[SUBARU] A surprise attack
from a new enemy.

24
00:01:57,333 --> 00:01:59,375
A daring escape from danger.

25
00:01:59,458 --> 00:02:02,041
Something relatable
in an extraordinary world.

26
00:02:02,125 --> 00:02:04,250
Something unexpected
in the mundane.

27
00:02:04,333 --> 00:02:05,291
A twist.

28
00:02:05,375 --> 00:02:07,833
-[TARO barking]
-[TANABE] Taro?

29
00:02:07,916 --> 00:02:10,041
My goodness! Watch out!

30
00:02:10,125 --> 00:02:12,500
Subaru!
The hose! Look!

31
00:02:12,583 --> 00:02:13,958
[grunting]

32
00:03:45,291 --> 00:03:47,666
[SUBARU]
I'm so sorry!

33
00:03:47,750 --> 00:03:50,333
I didn’t know
where I was pointing that.

34
00:03:50,416 --> 00:03:51,875
[TANABE chuckles]
Well, I was surprised,

35
00:03:51,958 --> 00:03:53,666
but it’s nothing
to apologize for.

36
00:03:53,750 --> 00:03:55,333
Taro loves a good bath!

37
00:03:55,416 --> 00:03:57,416
-Aw! Yes you do!
-[TARO barks]

38
00:03:57,500 --> 00:04:01,666
Actually, I’m the one who owes
you an apology, if anything.

39
00:04:01,750 --> 00:04:04,458
I already watered
Saho’s garden this morning.

40
00:04:04,541 --> 00:04:07,375
I had no idea you were
going to do it yourself!

41
00:04:07,458 --> 00:04:08,958
I don’t think
I’ve ever seen you

42
00:04:09,041 --> 00:04:11,458
taking care of her
flowers before.

43
00:04:15,125 --> 00:04:17,875
Wait, so you’ve been
looking after the garden

44
00:04:17,958 --> 00:04:20,083
all this time
and I never knew?

45
00:04:20,166 --> 00:04:22,833
I thought they looked awfully
healthy all things considered,

46
00:04:22,916 --> 00:04:25,000
but I’m hardly
a gardening expert.

47
00:04:25,083 --> 00:04:27,375
I was afraid I might be
overstepping my bounds.

48
00:04:27,458 --> 00:04:29,375
But when I was
watering my plants,

49
00:04:29,458 --> 00:04:32,041
I’d lift up the hose and spray!

50
00:04:32,125 --> 00:04:34,125
I should’ve asked
you first, though.

51
00:04:34,208 --> 00:04:36,208
Uh, no. Thank you.

52
00:04:36,291 --> 00:04:38,541
If nobody helped to water them,

53
00:04:38,625 --> 00:04:39,875
they’d be dead.

54
00:04:39,958 --> 00:04:41,333
It's fine.

55
00:04:41,416 --> 00:04:44,041
She took care of that garden
for you, after all.

56
00:04:44,125 --> 00:04:47,083
I didn’t want all her hard work
to go to waste, you know?

57
00:04:47,166 --> 00:04:48,916
[SUBARU]
She did this for me?

58
00:04:49,000 --> 00:04:50,458
Did you see those?

59
00:04:50,541 --> 00:04:54,166
I’m happy to see they’re
blooming again this year.

60
00:04:54,250 --> 00:04:55,375
And there!

61
00:04:56,666 --> 00:04:59,208
Every time you travel,
your garden gets bigger!

62
00:04:59,291 --> 00:05:01,375
You’ll have every flower
in the country soon!

63
00:05:01,458 --> 00:05:03,541
[laughs]
I doubt that!

64
00:05:03,625 --> 00:05:06,750
The lavender I bought in Furano
isn’t even blooming yet!

65
00:05:06,833 --> 00:05:09,000
I’m hoping the blueberries
from Ishikawa

66
00:05:09,083 --> 00:05:10,666
will bear fruit next spring.

67
00:05:10,750 --> 00:05:13,375
So, what are you
planting in that one?

68
00:05:13,458 --> 00:05:14,416
Oh, they’re cute.

69
00:05:14,500 --> 00:05:16,708
Baby Blue Eyes from Ibaraki.

70
00:05:16,791 --> 00:05:18,916
When I saw them,
I knew I had to have them!

71
00:05:19,000 --> 00:05:21,875
Blue is Subaru’s
favorite color, you know.

72
00:05:21,958 --> 00:05:23,833
I would love to show him
a whole field of these,

73
00:05:23,916 --> 00:05:27,125
but I’ll have to settle
for this for the time being.

74
00:05:27,208 --> 00:05:29,666
She used to tell me she hoped
you could enjoy these flowers

75
00:05:29,750 --> 00:05:30,916
from inside the house.

76
00:05:31,000 --> 00:05:32,416
Wherever she went,

77
00:05:32,500 --> 00:05:34,666
she brought back her
favorite plants as a souvenir.

78
00:05:34,750 --> 00:05:37,208
That way, she could
share the world with you.

79
00:05:38,375 --> 00:05:40,500
They were here all this time
and I never knew.

80
00:05:40,583 --> 00:05:43,083
-[TARO barks]
-[TANABE] Okay, okay, Taro!

81
00:05:43,166 --> 00:05:44,666
I'll walk you.

82
00:05:44,750 --> 00:05:46,916
Well, just look at them
from time to time, all right?

83
00:05:47,000 --> 00:05:48,875
They’re so pretty.
And after all,

84
00:05:48,958 --> 00:05:50,791
they were picked out
just for you!

85
00:05:50,875 --> 00:05:53,166
-[TARO barks]
-[TANABE] Hey, don’t run, Taro!

86
00:05:53,250 --> 00:05:55,458
-[TANABE yells, laughs]
-[TARO barks]

87
00:05:55,541 --> 00:05:57,958
♪

88
00:06:03,000 --> 00:06:04,000
[gasps]

89
00:06:08,500 --> 00:06:11,125
[chuckles]
You really outdid yourself, Mom.

90
00:06:11,208 --> 00:06:13,000
But that’s so like you.

91
00:06:16,125 --> 00:06:16,958
Huh?

92
00:06:18,291 --> 00:06:19,958
Guess Haru left.

93
00:06:20,041 --> 00:06:22,125
-[door sliding]
-Haru?

94
00:06:22,208 --> 00:06:24,250
[footsteps]

95
00:06:24,333 --> 00:06:25,500
Where are you?

96
00:06:25,583 --> 00:06:29,041
Did I scare her too much
with that hose?

97
00:06:33,875 --> 00:06:36,291
[gasps softly]
Somebody’s outside.

98
00:06:40,291 --> 00:06:42,750
Why are they just
standing there?

99
00:06:42,833 --> 00:06:44,125
[gasps]

100
00:06:44,208 --> 00:06:45,875
[SUBARU] Maybe they’re trying
to break in!

101
00:06:45,958 --> 00:06:48,291
Haru probably saw them
and went to hide somewhere!

102
00:06:51,875 --> 00:06:53,750
[gasps]
Hi, Mikazuki.

103
00:06:53,833 --> 00:06:56,250
[gasps]
So it’s just you.

104
00:06:56,333 --> 00:06:59,625
Why didn’t you ring
the doorbell, you big weirdo?

105
00:06:59,708 --> 00:07:01,208
[KAWASE]
Uh, well,

106
00:07:01,291 --> 00:07:03,291
there was a young man
here, acting a bit strange,

107
00:07:03,375 --> 00:07:05,833
but he seemed to be on a first
name basis with you.

108
00:07:05,916 --> 00:07:08,000
Where did he go?

109
00:07:08,083 --> 00:07:09,958
Nobody calls me
by my first name.

110
00:07:10,041 --> 00:07:11,291
Only Hiroto.

111
00:07:11,375 --> 00:07:12,375
[KAWASE]
What?

112
00:07:12,458 --> 00:07:13,708
You don’t even
have a cousin

113
00:07:13,791 --> 00:07:16,750
-or something like that?
-[door squeaks open]

114
00:07:16,833 --> 00:07:18,875
If he’s not someone
you know, then...

115
00:07:18,958 --> 00:07:21,500
-Uh-oh...
-[grunting]

116
00:07:21,583 --> 00:07:24,041
-[YUGO] Please, forgive me!
-[KAWASE screaming]

117
00:07:24,125 --> 00:07:26,083
[BOTH whimpering]

118
00:07:30,583 --> 00:07:33,000
Oh, wait. It... it’s you!

119
00:07:33,083 --> 00:07:34,791
Okami’s brother, right?

120
00:07:34,875 --> 00:07:36,291
Yugo, was it?

121
00:07:40,333 --> 00:07:41,875
I'm so sorry.

122
00:07:41,958 --> 00:07:43,375
I knew it might
be kind of awkward

123
00:07:43,458 --> 00:07:45,041
if I just showed up
at your house.

124
00:07:45,125 --> 00:07:48,041
But I had to apologize.

125
00:07:48,125 --> 00:07:51,833
I mean, the way I acted
when we first met...

126
00:07:51,916 --> 00:07:56,083
I grabbed you, said you were
creepin’ on my sister.

127
00:07:56,166 --> 00:07:57,875
-[KAWASE gasping]
-Yeah, but we worked out

128
00:07:57,958 --> 00:07:59,958
the misunderstanding,
so it’s fine.

129
00:08:00,041 --> 00:08:01,916
[YUGO] And I kept talking
about your story,

130
00:08:02,000 --> 00:08:04,833
but I didn’t realize
you were the Mikazuki.

131
00:08:04,916 --> 00:08:07,583
Ever since I found out
who you are,

132
00:08:07,666 --> 00:08:10,125
I’ve been dying
to apologize to you.

133
00:08:10,208 --> 00:08:11,708
But I kept wussing out,

134
00:08:11,791 --> 00:08:13,583
‘cause I was afraid
you might be mad at me.

135
00:08:13,666 --> 00:08:16,083
I thought
you wouldn’t listen.

136
00:08:16,166 --> 00:08:19,083
I didn’t mean for it
to take this long.

137
00:08:19,166 --> 00:08:21,916
I’m sorry, bro.
For real.

138
00:08:22,000 --> 00:08:24,041
No, it wasn’t a big deal
to me, I promise!

139
00:08:24,125 --> 00:08:25,583
[YUGO]
You know,

140
00:08:25,666 --> 00:08:28,625
I really get excited
when I read your stories.

141
00:08:28,708 --> 00:08:30,625
It’s like I’m invincible.

142
00:08:30,708 --> 00:08:32,666
Like anything’s possible.

143
00:08:34,250 --> 00:08:37,041
I wanna work hard,
try new things.

144
00:08:37,125 --> 00:08:38,708
I don't know,
it’s hard to explain,

145
00:08:38,791 --> 00:08:41,625
but your writing
gives me courage.

146
00:08:41,708 --> 00:08:43,833
I’ll always be here
cheering for you.

147
00:08:43,916 --> 00:08:45,375
[SUBARU]
N-no! Please!

148
00:08:46,750 --> 00:08:49,375
I mean, I’m grateful.

149
00:08:49,458 --> 00:08:51,958
Don’t thank me!
It’s nothing!

150
00:08:52,041 --> 00:08:54,166
I owe you for hearing me out!

151
00:08:55,750 --> 00:08:56,833
[YUGO sighs]

152
00:08:56,916 --> 00:08:58,666
Can’t believe
I finally said it.

153
00:09:01,000 --> 00:09:02,375
[SUBARU]
This is new for me.

154
00:09:02,458 --> 00:09:05,583
Feeling joy. Feeling regret.

155
00:09:05,666 --> 00:09:09,083
Being moved by just a few,
simple words.

156
00:09:09,166 --> 00:09:12,208
I don’t know how it happened.

157
00:09:13,625 --> 00:09:16,041
But these days,
all of a sudden,

158
00:09:16,125 --> 00:09:18,958
my heart feels
so much fuller.

159
00:09:21,958 --> 00:09:26,875
When was it
that my life started to change?

160
00:09:29,458 --> 00:09:30,958
[door opens]

161
00:09:31,041 --> 00:09:32,916
[YUGO]
Thanks again for having me, bro.

162
00:09:33,000 --> 00:09:35,375
[KAWASE]
He’s a good kid, isn’t he?

163
00:09:35,458 --> 00:09:36,666
[SUBARU]
Yeah.

164
00:09:36,750 --> 00:09:39,791
Haru seemed to be
awful fond of him, too.

165
00:09:39,875 --> 00:09:41,250
If he’s got some trick,

166
00:09:41,333 --> 00:09:43,208
I sure wish
he’d share it with me, though.

167
00:09:43,291 --> 00:09:45,208
[SUBARU]
Huh? Trick?

168
00:09:45,291 --> 00:09:46,625
I don't know.

169
00:09:46,708 --> 00:09:48,791
Haru seemed to like
Yugo right from the start.

170
00:09:48,875 --> 00:09:50,625
Oh, to be loved!

171
00:09:50,708 --> 00:09:53,708
Oh! By the way,
have any good ideas yet?

172
00:09:53,791 --> 00:09:56,666
-For your new series?
-[SUBARU gasps]

173
00:09:56,750 --> 00:09:58,208
[SUBARU groans]

174
00:09:58,291 --> 00:10:01,708
I, uh, guess that’s a “no.”

175
00:10:01,791 --> 00:10:03,166
I’m sorry.

176
00:10:03,250 --> 00:10:05,166
It seems I’m
suffering from writer’s block.

177
00:10:05,250 --> 00:10:08,208
Listen,
this is just a thought,

178
00:10:08,291 --> 00:10:10,125
but have you
considered traveling?

179
00:10:10,208 --> 00:10:12,166
Maybe for a change
of perspective?

180
00:10:12,250 --> 00:10:13,416
[SUBARU inhales sharply]

181
00:10:13,500 --> 00:10:15,416
No, of course
you haven’t, right?

182
00:10:15,500 --> 00:10:16,958
[SUBARU]
That’s a good idea.

183
00:10:17,041 --> 00:10:18,208
[KAWASE gasps in shock]

184
00:10:18,291 --> 00:10:21,041
Why are you surprised?

185
00:10:21,125 --> 00:10:23,416
It was your suggestion,
wasn’t it?

186
00:10:23,500 --> 00:10:25,500
Well, yes, it was,
but when we first met,

187
00:10:25,583 --> 00:10:27,250
I couldn’t even get you
to come outside.

188
00:10:27,333 --> 00:10:29,000
So this is new!

189
00:10:31,000 --> 00:10:35,750
Sorry, I mean, just tell me
when you decide where to go.

190
00:10:35,833 --> 00:10:38,916
Let me handle it.
I’ll make it happen.

191
00:10:39,000 --> 00:10:40,250
Thanks.

192
00:10:41,583 --> 00:10:43,250
[SUBARU]
Taking a trip, huh?

193
00:10:43,333 --> 00:10:45,875
[food clattering in bowl]

194
00:10:47,916 --> 00:10:51,375
[eager munching]

195
00:10:53,166 --> 00:10:56,208
Okay, but where? [sighs]

196
00:10:56,291 --> 00:10:57,375
[door sliding]

197
00:11:07,875 --> 00:11:10,458
I wonder what happened
with that one.

198
00:11:10,541 --> 00:11:12,583
I don’t think
anything’s ever grown there.

199
00:11:14,375 --> 00:11:17,625
Huh. Guess she did
try to plant something.

200
00:11:17,708 --> 00:11:20,125
-[SUBARU gasping]
-[SUBARU'S MOM] Hey, Subaru.

201
00:11:20,208 --> 00:11:23,958
Next time, maybe we can
all take a trip, together.

202
00:11:24,041 --> 00:11:26,750
See you when we get back!

203
00:11:26,833 --> 00:11:29,291
[SUBARU shuddering]

204
00:11:36,791 --> 00:11:38,750
[KAWASE]
Tokushima?

205
00:11:38,833 --> 00:11:42,708
Shikoku, huh?
That sounds dandy!

206
00:11:42,791 --> 00:11:46,250
I’ll book you a flight
and hotel ASAP!

207
00:11:46,333 --> 00:11:49,750
[SUBARU] Thanks. That’ll save me
a lot of trouble.

208
00:11:49,833 --> 00:11:52,875
I’ve never gone on a trip
like this in my life.

209
00:11:52,958 --> 00:11:55,250
[KAWASE] Hey, no problem.
Happy to help.

210
00:11:55,333 --> 00:11:56,458
Wait!

211
00:11:56,541 --> 00:11:59,541
What are you gonna
do about Haru?

212
00:11:59,625 --> 00:12:01,541
Huh? I’m confused.

213
00:12:01,625 --> 00:12:03,708
[KAWASE]
Well, you’ll be gone.

214
00:12:03,791 --> 00:12:06,083
Don’t you need someone to look
after her till you get back?

215
00:12:07,583 --> 00:12:09,958
[KAWASE]
I didn’t think of that.

216
00:12:11,375 --> 00:12:13,875
[birds chirping]

217
00:12:23,291 --> 00:12:24,750
[SUBARU grumbles]

218
00:12:26,500 --> 00:12:27,458
[inhales sharply]

219
00:12:27,541 --> 00:12:28,875
[NANA]
Going on a trip, huh?

220
00:12:28,958 --> 00:12:31,625
[SUBARU] Yeah. It’s just
two days and one night,

221
00:12:31,708 --> 00:12:33,750
but I’m worried about
leaving her alone.

222
00:12:33,833 --> 00:12:37,541
In that case, it’s probably best
to put her in a pet hotel.

223
00:12:37,625 --> 00:12:40,208
-[SUBARU] Is that a thing?
-Yeah.

224
00:12:40,291 --> 00:12:42,833
I’ll give you the phone number
to a good one, okay?

225
00:12:42,916 --> 00:12:46,458
[SUBARU] First, I gotta
get Haru into the cat carrier.

226
00:12:46,541 --> 00:12:47,875
Haru!

227
00:12:50,000 --> 00:12:51,625
Haru!

228
00:12:51,708 --> 00:12:54,375
♪

229
00:12:57,041 --> 00:12:58,375
She’s coming!

230
00:13:03,208 --> 00:13:06,583
[SUBARU] Yes! It’s working!
Just like Okami said!

231
00:13:06,666 --> 00:13:08,916
The last time
you used the carrier

232
00:13:09,000 --> 00:13:10,833
was to take her
to the vet, right?

233
00:13:10,916 --> 00:13:12,375
That’s tricky.

234
00:13:12,458 --> 00:13:15,083
She probably won't get inside
on her own after that.

235
00:13:15,166 --> 00:13:16,750
For a lot of cats,

236
00:13:16,833 --> 00:13:19,166
getting in the carrier
means going someplace bad,

237
00:13:19,250 --> 00:13:20,833
so you have to get
a little creative.

238
00:13:20,916 --> 00:13:22,375
Try this.

239
00:13:22,458 --> 00:13:24,250
[SUBARU]
Look, Haru! A treat!

240
00:13:24,333 --> 00:13:26,458
[HARU meows]

241
00:13:26,541 --> 00:13:28,750
[SUBARU] Nailed it!
That was too easy!

242
00:13:28,833 --> 00:13:31,250
Now’s my chance!

243
00:13:31,333 --> 00:13:33,875
-Uh-oh!
-[HARU meowing]

244
00:13:33,958 --> 00:13:37,500
-[SUBARU] Hey! Settle down!
-[HARU meowing angrily]

245
00:13:37,583 --> 00:13:40,666
[angry meowing continues]

246
00:13:42,708 --> 00:13:46,541
Haru?
Hey! You alive?

247
00:13:58,333 --> 00:14:01,208
-Nope. Not gonna work.
-[eager munching]

248
00:14:01,291 --> 00:14:04,750
-[pellets clattering]
-[SUBARU] And stop.

249
00:14:04,833 --> 00:14:06,750
[HIROTO]
Twenty-eight grams?

250
00:14:06,833 --> 00:14:08,875
You sure that’s enough for her?

251
00:14:08,958 --> 00:14:10,208
Uh-huh.

252
00:14:10,291 --> 00:14:11,916
Cats are supposed to eat
several small meals,

253
00:14:12,000 --> 00:14:13,750
so keep it under 35.

254
00:14:13,833 --> 00:14:16,125
Usually three times a day.

255
00:14:16,208 --> 00:14:18,291
I’ll feed her a serving
before I leave.

256
00:14:18,375 --> 00:14:21,041
Try to come by at least
once after that, if you can.

257
00:14:21,125 --> 00:14:22,791
[HIROTO]
No prob.

258
00:14:22,875 --> 00:14:24,166
[pellets clattering]

259
00:14:24,250 --> 00:14:26,208
Looked like
about this much, I think?

260
00:14:28,208 --> 00:14:30,500
[SUBARU]
Wow, how did you pull that off?

261
00:14:30,583 --> 00:14:32,583
[HIROTO] Eh, I used to measure
milk for my sister

262
00:14:32,666 --> 00:14:34,041
when she was a baby.

263
00:14:34,125 --> 00:14:35,458
Stop it!

264
00:14:35,541 --> 00:14:37,458
You just had dinner
a second ago!

265
00:14:37,541 --> 00:14:39,791
For a little cat,
she’s still a big eater, huh?

266
00:14:39,875 --> 00:14:43,041
Yeah, so don’t give her too
much, even if she complains.

267
00:14:43,125 --> 00:14:45,083
She’s still on a diet.

268
00:14:45,166 --> 00:14:46,708
Okay, sure.

269
00:14:46,791 --> 00:14:48,916
I still can’t believe
you’re going on a trip, though.

270
00:14:49,000 --> 00:14:50,541
This is crazy!

271
00:14:50,625 --> 00:14:53,583
You’ll have to hold down
the fort while he’s gone, Haru!

272
00:14:53,666 --> 00:14:57,125
So don’t cry.
You gotta be tough, okay?

273
00:14:59,625 --> 00:15:00,916
[SUBARU gasps]

274
00:15:01,000 --> 00:15:02,208
[laughs quietly]

275
00:15:02,291 --> 00:15:04,791
[phone jingles, vibrates]

276
00:15:04,875 --> 00:15:07,083
It’s Kawase. Hello?

277
00:15:07,166 --> 00:15:10,625
Oh, good. Yeah, thank you.

278
00:15:10,708 --> 00:15:14,125
Uh-huh. Let me write
that down real quick.

279
00:15:15,625 --> 00:15:18,000
Okay, go ahead.

280
00:15:18,083 --> 00:15:20,416
Nagami Hotel.

281
00:15:20,500 --> 00:15:22,583
Pension Iwakuni.

282
00:15:22,666 --> 00:15:25,583
Shijima.
Shijima House?

283
00:15:25,666 --> 00:15:27,458
If you need anything,

284
00:15:27,541 --> 00:15:30,333
the place where we’re
staying is on the fridge, okay?

285
00:15:31,916 --> 00:15:34,541
[crying]

286
00:15:37,083 --> 00:15:39,708
[SUBARU] Shijima House.
I’ll take that one.

287
00:15:42,208 --> 00:15:44,750
Yeah. Yeah. Thanks again.

288
00:15:44,833 --> 00:15:46,333
That where you’re staying?

289
00:15:46,416 --> 00:15:48,833
[SUBARU]
Mm-hmm. Shijima House.

290
00:15:48,916 --> 00:15:51,291
It has to be.

291
00:15:51,375 --> 00:15:55,125
♪

292
00:16:00,000 --> 00:16:03,250
Haru. I’ll see you soon.

293
00:16:05,916 --> 00:16:08,250
[door sliding open,
then closed]

294
00:16:09,916 --> 00:16:12,666
[airplane roaring]

295
00:16:16,166 --> 00:16:19,416
[LADY] We’ve been
expecting you, Mr. Mikazuki!

296
00:16:19,500 --> 00:16:22,166
Here, this is your room.

297
00:16:22,250 --> 00:16:24,208
It’s nice. Thank you.

298
00:16:33,000 --> 00:16:35,541
[LADY]
Um, can I ask you a question?

299
00:16:35,625 --> 00:16:38,333
-Uh-huh?
-It was about three years ago,

300
00:16:38,416 --> 00:16:40,916
but you made a reservation
with us before, didn’t you?

301
00:16:41,000 --> 00:16:41,958
[SUBARU gasps]

302
00:16:42,041 --> 00:16:44,625
[SUBARU]
Yeah, or my parents did.

303
00:16:44,708 --> 00:16:46,375
I thought so.

304
00:16:46,458 --> 00:16:49,916
Your name is so unique.
It stuck with me all this time!

305
00:16:50,000 --> 00:16:52,083
And let’s see...

306
00:16:52,166 --> 00:16:56,208
If I recall correctly,
it was a reservation for three.

307
00:16:56,291 --> 00:16:57,958
For three?

308
00:16:58,041 --> 00:16:59,583
[LADY] We got a call
from the travel agency

309
00:16:59,666 --> 00:17:02,666
at the very last minute,
saying you had canceled.

310
00:17:02,750 --> 00:17:06,208
So, I’m glad you decided to
come back after all this time.

311
00:17:06,291 --> 00:17:07,750
Please enjoy your tea.

312
00:17:10,875 --> 00:17:13,750
[SUBARU]
Mom held out to the very end.

313
00:17:13,833 --> 00:17:17,208
She never gave up on inviting me
till the day they left.

314
00:17:17,291 --> 00:17:19,958
And that trip was the same.

315
00:17:20,041 --> 00:17:21,458
They held that reservation,

316
00:17:21,541 --> 00:17:24,250
hoping I would finally
change my mind.

317
00:17:34,916 --> 00:17:36,083
[SUBARU]
I came here.

318
00:17:36,166 --> 00:17:40,041
But I don’t know
what I hoped to find.

319
00:17:44,666 --> 00:17:48,125
Interested in how
the locals make indigo dye?

320
00:17:48,208 --> 00:17:51,666
A little bit.
You’re famous for it.

321
00:17:51,750 --> 00:17:55,708
In Tokushima, the dye used in
indigo is called “awa-ai."

322
00:17:55,791 --> 00:17:57,791
The process that
craftsmen use to make it

323
00:17:57,875 --> 00:17:59,958
is the same as it
was generations ago.

324
00:18:01,708 --> 00:18:03,958
I didn’t know there were
so many shades of blue.

325
00:18:04,041 --> 00:18:05,541
[LADY] Don’t tell me.

326
00:18:05,625 --> 00:18:07,750
Did you come here because
you’re a blue enthusiast?

327
00:18:07,833 --> 00:18:08,791
[SUBARU]
Uh--

328
00:18:08,875 --> 00:18:10,125
[LADY]
I can’t blame you.

329
00:18:10,208 --> 00:18:12,333
That sweater
does look nice on you.

330
00:18:12,416 --> 00:18:14,750
♪

331
00:18:14,833 --> 00:18:16,583
[inaudible]

332
00:18:18,833 --> 00:18:20,833
[SUBARU'S MOM]
Look at that! I just knew it!

333
00:18:20,916 --> 00:18:23,708
That sweater had your name
written all over it!

334
00:18:23,791 --> 00:18:26,958
Come on.
It’s no big deal.

335
00:18:27,041 --> 00:18:29,458
It is to me.
I picked it out myself,

336
00:18:29,541 --> 00:18:32,000
and you look so handsome in it!

337
00:18:34,750 --> 00:18:38,375
[footsteps]

338
00:18:42,750 --> 00:18:45,750
-[wind whistling]
-[fabric flapping]

339
00:18:52,166 --> 00:18:55,000
[SUBARU'S MOM] My gosh,
you’re wearing that again?

340
00:18:55,083 --> 00:18:57,750
Huh? Why not?

341
00:18:57,833 --> 00:19:00,583
Well, don’t get me wrong,
I’m really happy you like it.

342
00:19:00,666 --> 00:19:04,041
But since you wear it so often,
it’s starting to fade a bit.

343
00:19:04,125 --> 00:19:07,000
-[SUBARU] Is it?
-You didn’t notice?

344
00:19:07,083 --> 00:19:10,000
It was the loveliest color
when we bought it. [gasps]

345
00:19:10,083 --> 00:19:13,000
Hey! Honey, I just
thought of something!

346
00:19:13,083 --> 00:19:14,791
Remember when we went
to Kochi?

347
00:19:15,791 --> 00:19:18,041
[SUBARU]
Mom? Dad?

348
00:19:19,583 --> 00:19:22,041
The place you wanted
to go with me.

349
00:19:23,500 --> 00:19:26,041
The thing you wanted me
to me see.

350
00:19:27,750 --> 00:19:30,000
Was it here?

351
00:19:30,083 --> 00:19:31,416
[crying]

352
00:19:31,500 --> 00:19:34,458
[SUBARU] No matter how much
I think about it,

353
00:19:34,541 --> 00:19:37,125
or how many times I ask,

354
00:19:37,208 --> 00:19:39,000
I’ll never hear their answer.

355
00:19:40,750 --> 00:19:45,083
But I’m here now.
At least I have that.

356
00:20:00,583 --> 00:20:02,666
[SUBARU]
On second thought,

357
00:20:02,750 --> 00:20:05,500
maybe I should have
brought her with me.

358
00:20:05,583 --> 00:20:06,541
Uh--

359
00:20:14,750 --> 00:20:18,083
[HARU] Shoot.
Did I sleep all day again?

360
00:20:19,708 --> 00:20:22,541
[yawning loudly]

361
00:20:26,708 --> 00:20:30,208
Huh? It’s dark,
but he’s still not back yet?

362
00:20:32,375 --> 00:20:33,625
[lapping]

363
00:20:33,708 --> 00:20:36,208
Well, that’s okay.
I’ll keep napping.

364
00:20:36,291 --> 00:20:37,833
He’ll be here by morning.

365
00:20:37,916 --> 00:20:41,500
I bet he’ll be all worked up
about something.

366
00:20:41,583 --> 00:20:43,375
Just like always.

367
00:20:48,458 --> 00:20:50,250
[sniffing]

368
00:21:02,333 --> 00:21:04,625
[yawning loudly]

369
00:21:12,791 --> 00:21:15,208
[LADY] Hmm?
You’re looking for flower seeds?

370
00:21:15,291 --> 00:21:17,958
Uh-huh.
Or a seedling, maybe?

371
00:21:18,041 --> 00:21:20,791
Something this area’s
famous for, if possible.

372
00:21:20,875 --> 00:21:23,375
[LADY] There’s a shopping center
nearby with a nursery.

373
00:21:23,458 --> 00:21:25,875
But it’s in the opposite
direction of the airport

374
00:21:25,958 --> 00:21:27,708
and the weather’s looking bad.

375
00:21:27,791 --> 00:21:29,208
[OLD LADY]
Who needs a nursery?

376
00:21:29,291 --> 00:21:32,875
We’ve got indigo right
in our own back yard.

377
00:21:32,958 --> 00:21:35,291
You just wait there one second.

378
00:21:35,375 --> 00:21:36,833
I’ll go fetch you some.

379
00:21:36,916 --> 00:21:38,625
Uh, are you sure?

380
00:21:38,708 --> 00:21:41,750
[OLD LADY] We’ve got plenty!
No trouble at all!

381
00:21:41,833 --> 00:21:44,125
[door slides open, closed]

382
00:21:44,208 --> 00:21:46,541
Our Indigo should fit the bill,
I’d think.

383
00:21:46,625 --> 00:21:48,916
-Yeah, but...
-It’s fine to take it.

384
00:21:49,000 --> 00:21:51,416
-She’s the owner, after all.
-[SUBARU gasps]

385
00:21:51,500 --> 00:21:53,958
[thunder rumbling]

386
00:21:58,708 --> 00:22:02,083
[OLD LADY] Here you go.
Hope that does it.

387
00:22:02,166 --> 00:22:03,416
Thanks for your trouble.

388
00:22:03,500 --> 00:22:05,916
You're very welcome.

389
00:22:06,000 --> 00:22:08,750
You got that wet
just stepping out?

390
00:22:08,833 --> 00:22:10,916
[OLD LADY]
Oh, yes. Frightful weather.

391
00:22:11,000 --> 00:22:13,291
-[SUBARU] What?
-[rain pouring]

392
00:22:14,458 --> 00:22:16,000
[shudders]

393
00:22:19,208 --> 00:22:20,916
No.

394
00:22:22,125 --> 00:22:24,000
You gotta be kidding.

395
00:23:56,875 --> 00:23:59,416
-[HARU] Nice weather.
-[TARO] It sure is.

396
00:23:59,500 --> 00:24:01,666
[HARU] I wish it would stay
like this all the time.

397
00:24:01,750 --> 00:24:03,541
-[TARO] Me, too.
-[HARU] I guess happiness

398
00:24:03,625 --> 00:24:05,625
is only a sunny day away, huh?

